Duplicate Report


T-code → ZDUPINV - Advanced SImilar Invoice Report 

CAG - Data Download

1.	Enter into SM37 and look for the daily automatic job:

D_FIAPDUPINVREP

 

2.	Select the job and click on Spool 

 

3.	Click on Type

 

4.	Download the data into a Google Sheets

 

5.	Paste the data into the daily template and, if necessary, scroll down the formulas from M to Q

 

6.	Copy and paste the lines that are under “Review Possible Duplicate” to the third tab and assign a case number in column A (considering the last case number assigned to the previous day cases)

 

7.	From FBL1N, download the document numbers from this final tab to get the correct amount sign. Once downloaded, paste it into the daily template and, with a VLOOKUP formula, bring the correct amounts to the ‘Final’ sheet:
 

 

8.	Paste the final data into the consolidated Duplicate Report
9.	Block in SAP (from tcode FBL1N) all the items under ‘UNPAID’ status in column L with payment block B (this will help us prevent duplicate payments)


I&E - Assignment


1.	In T-code ZVIM_VA2 look for the document numbers:
Fields to be completed:
-	Supplier with the vendor numbers from column E
-	Accounting Document Number with the document numbers from column C
-	Reference with the invoice numbers from column D
-	Company Code with *

 

2.	Download the data and paste it into the Duplicate Report in tab ‘Doc Type’ (it is cumulative)

 
 
3.	If necessary, scroll down the formulas from columns S-U:

 

4.	To assign the cases, I&E team looks at column S and, depending on the type of document, they assign it to the corresponding team. 
If a document brings N/A, then they search the document into FBL1N to determine who processed it. 
